properties.name: SDK Village Green LLC
properties.description:
Come experience life inside a one- or two-bedroom apartment at SDK Village Green Apartments today. Outfitted with private patios, spacious cabinets, and matching appliances, these homes have it all.

Conveniently located near Highway 46 and Interstate 80, the area’s most popular shopping destinations are mere moments away. Spend an afternoon strolling and shopping at the pedestrian-friendly enclosed Ledgewood Mall. Home to renowned retailers like Marshall’s, Macy’s, and Ashley Furniture, this place has it all. For all of your food and kitchen-preparation needs, there are many grocers nearby, including ShopRite, Weis Market, and BJ’s Wholesale Club.

When you’d rather enjoy a meal outside your home, there are many great restaurants to choose from. Treat yourself to the taste of authentic Italian fare at Branda’s Italian Grill. Offering classic fare like Chicken Marsala, specialty pizzas, and more, this place is unlike any other. For something a little less formal, check out Budd Lake Diner. This popular American diner specializes in the classics, including burgers and a range of hot and cold sandwiches, and provides top-notch service along with them. Satisfy your cravings for Chinese and Southeast Asian cuisine at King Wok. This family-run establishment uses only the freshest ingredients to create their authentic offerings. Regulars rave about the dumplings, chow mein, and pan-fried noodles.

Please call for an appointment today!

properties.name: The Park View At 320
properties.description:
The Park View at 320 is a luxury rental community with 273 spacious apartment units. The building is comprised of studios, one, two and three bedroom apartments. Conveniently located next to the historic Brick Church Station(NJ transit) and within a 25 minute train ride to Manhattan, this 20 story building offers breathtaking views of the picturesque Orange mountains and Manhattan skyline.

The Park View at 320 is commonly referred to as "The Jewel of Essex County" and is the most exclusive and desirable address within the city of East Orange. Residents will enjoy many amenities within the building, that are similarly offered in Manhattan's finest luxury apartments, including cutting edge security, concierge call back, a 24-hour security guard, fitness center, swimming pool, grand lobby, designed landscaping and on-site laundry facilities! In addition, the on-site superintendent is present to ensure that all maintenance issues are handled immediately. Off-street parking is just one more reason that residents can feel at ease when living at The Park View at 320. The units feature hardwood flooring throughout, central air/heating systems, upgraded kitchen cabinets, Stainless steel appliance package(Select Units Only!!!), and many additional upgrades. Exclusive units include a private balcony that capture the tranquility of the Manhattan skyline and enhance the magnificent views.

properties.name: SDK Greenbrook Gardens
properties.description:
Greenbrook Gardens is a beautiful apartment community in Plainfield, NJ, offering one- and two-bedroom apartments located a short distance from Washington Rock Park. With easy access to Highways 22 and 28, residents are always minutes away from shops, restaurants, and entertainment.

If you’re looking for authentic Peruvian cuisine, you’ll enjoy eating at Tradiciones de mi Pueblo. They offer a menu with traditional Peruvian favorites, such as ceviche, bandeja paisa, chicharrones, and Peruvian roasted chicken. Greenbrook Gardens is also a short distance away from Amazing Taste. Local residents recommend their favorite dishes to first-time visitors. You can enjoy jerk chicken, yellow rice, fried tilapia, banana pudding, and more.

After you enjoy a nice lunch, you can visit shopping centers in the Plainfield area. Find the latest styles and trends at Watchung Square Mall. This shopping center features great retail stores, such as ULTA Beauty, Bed Bath and Beyond, Target, Staples, Walmart and The Home Depot. Blue Star Shopping Center, also located near Greenbrook Gardens, is a great shopping destination with stores such as Kohl’s, Michaels, Petco, Dollar Tree, Toys R Us, Marshalls, GameStop, and GNC. You can visit Eight on the Break, St. Joseph Bingo Hall, and North Plainfield Exempt Firemen’s Association Museum, which are all a short distance from Greenbrook Gardens.

Speak to a staff member from the Greenbrook Gardens leasing office to learn more information about your new neighborhood.
